# AGENTS.md Lifecycle Rule

`AGENTS.md` is the AI context file committed to GitHub repos. It tells any agent (Cursor, Claude, GPT) everything they need to know about the project without reading the full codebase.

## Two versions

| Version | Location | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Local** | `~/.mission-control/agents-md/<repo-slug>/AGENTS.md` | Editable, always up to date, used immediately |
| **Repo** | `<repo-root>/AGENTS.md` | Committed, reviewed, merged via PR |

## Editing workflow

1. Always edit the **local** version first: `~/.mission-control/agents-md/<repo>/AGENTS.md`
2. When ready to publish: create a PR from the local version
3. Dashboard tracks PR status: `local` → `pr_open` → `merged`
4. After merge, the repo version and local version stay in sync

## Symlink for immediate use

The installer creates a symlink so Cursor picks up the local version immediately:
```bash
ln -sf ~/.mission-control/agents-md/<repo>/AGENTS.md <repo-root>/AGENTS.md
```

## Required AGENTS.md sections

```markdown
# AGENTS.md — <Project Name>

## What this project does
<1-2 sentences>

## Architecture
<Service map, key components>

## Key services and their ports/hosts
<Table or bullet list>

## Databases
<Connection patterns, not credentials>

## Key environment variables
<Names only, no values>

## How to run locally
<Commands>

## How to run tests
<Commands>

## Coding conventions
<Language, formatting, patterns to follow>

## Do not touch
<Files or directories agents must never modify>

## Current focus
<Active work, tickets, what the team is working on>
```

## Keep it lean
AGENTS.md is loaded into every agent context. Keep it under 200 lines. Deep knowledge goes in `~/.mission-control/docs/`.
